# Elements and Components

## Elements

- Constructor takes a **single options object**: `{ page, selector, text }`. Use either `selector` or `text` for one element, not both.
- The locator is stored in `this._element` (set in `BaseElement`).
- `Button` extends `BaseElement` and adds `click()`; `TextArea` extends `Button` and adds `type()`, `hasValue()`.
- When creating Elements from page objects or components, always pass one object.

```javascript
// BAD
new Button(this.page, '[class="navbar-brand"]');

// GOOD
new Button({ page: this.page, selector: '[class="navbar-brand"]' });
new Button({ page: this.page, text: "Get started" });
```

## Components

- Receive `page` (or an options object) in the constructor; compose Elements.
- When creating Elements inside components, use the same object form: `{ page: this.page, selector: "..." }` or `{ page: this.page, text: "..." }`.
